### EduNexus AI API Test Requests
### Make sure the server is running on http://localhost:3000

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:3000/health

###

### Generate Study Notes
POST http://localhost:3000/api/ai/generate-notes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Photosynthesis is the process by which plants convert light energy into chemical energy. During this process, plants use sunlight, carbon dioxide, and water to produce glucose and oxygen. The process occurs in the chloroplasts of plant cells, specifically in the thylakoid membranes where chlorophyll captures light energy.",
  "options": {
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "style": "academic",
    "language": "en",
    "includeExamples": true,
    "includeQuestions": true,
    "maxLength": 2000
  }
}

###

### Generate Quiz
POST http://localhost:3000/api/ai/generate-quiz
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "The water cycle, also known as the hydrological cycle, describes the continuous movement of water within the Earth and atmosphere. It involves processes such as evaporation, condensation, precipitation, and collection. Water evaporates from oceans, lakes, and rivers, forms clouds through condensation, and returns to Earth as precipitation.",
  "options": {
    "questionCount": 4,
    "difficulty": "easy",
    "questionTypes": ["multiple-choice", "true-false", "short-answer"],
    "subject": "Environmental Science",
    "language": "en"
  }
}

###

### Answer Question
POST http://localhost:3000/api/ai/answer-question
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "What is the main purpose of photosynthesis?",
  "context": "Photosynthesis is the process by which plants convert light energy into chemical energy. During this process, plants use sunlight, carbon dioxide, and water to produce glucose and oxygen. The process occurs in the chloroplasts of plant cells, specifically in the thylakoid membranes where chlorophyll captures light energy.",
  "options": {
    "language": "en",
    "includeSource": true,
    "maxLength": 300
  }
}

###

### Translate Content
POST http://localhost:3000/api/ai/translate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Machine learning is a subset of artificial intelligence that enables computers to learn and improve from experience without being explicitly programmed.",
  "targetLanguage": "es",
  "options": {
    "preserveFormatting": true,
    "educationalOptimization": true,
    "confidenceThreshold": 0.8
  }
}

###

### Generate Flashcards
POST http://localhost:3000/api/ai/generate-flashcards
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Photosynthesis is the process by which plants convert light energy into chemical energy. During this process, plants use sunlight, carbon dioxide, and water to produce glucose and oxygen. The process occurs in the chloroplasts of plant cells, specifically in the thylakoid membranes where chlorophyll captures light energy.",
  "options": {
    "cardCount": 5,
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "cardType": "basic",
    "language": "en",
    "includeImages": false,
    "includeAudio": false,
    "subject": "Biology"
  }
}

